(43, 13, 24, 42, 5, 7, 7, 'beckoned', 'Beckoning for Help', 'This connection highlights the act of beckoning in both passages. In John 13:24, Peter beckons to inquire about Jesus'' words, while in Luke 5:7, the fishermen beckon their partners for assistance. Both instances illustrate the theme of seeking help or clarification.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 24, 44, 12, 17, 17, NULL, 'Beckoning and Communication', 'This connection highlights the act of beckoning as a means of communication in both passages. In John 13:24, Peter beckons to inquire about Jesus'' words, while in Acts 12:17, the speaker beckons to communicate important news.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 24, 44, 13, 16, 16, NULL, 'Beckoning for Attention', 'This connection highlights the act of beckoning in both passages, where Simon Peter beckons to inquire about Jesus'' words and Paul beckons to gain the audience''s attention. Both instances illustrate a call for focus and engagement from their respective audiences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
